---
import Layout from '@/layouts/layout.astro'
import SignedInBanner from '@/components/common/signed-in-banner'
import { LandingFooter, LandingNavbar } from '@/components/landing'
---

<Layout title="About Kyoto">
  <SignedInBanner client:idle />
  <LandingNavbar />
  <main
    class="flex flex-col bg-linear-to-b from-background via-muted/10 to-background text-foreground"
  >
    <section class="relative border-b border-border/60 bg-background">
      <div
        class="container grid gap-10 px-6 py-24 sm:px-8 lg:grid-cols-[2fr,3fr] lg:gap-16"
      >
        <div class="space-y-6">
          <span
            class="inline-flex items-center rounded-full border border-border bg-muted px-3 py-1 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-muted-foreground"
          >
            Our Story
          </span>
          <h1 class="text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight sm:text-5xl">
            Helping teams ship quality software with confidence.
          </h1>
          <p class="text-base text-muted-foreground sm:text-lg">
            Kyoto was born from countless late-night releases and a shared
            belief that AI can make shipping software calmer. We build tools
            that let product teams focus on outcomes while Kyoto safeguards
            every deploy.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div
          class="grid gap-6 rounded-2xl border border-border bg-card p-8 shadow-sm"
        >
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">What we&apos;re building</h2>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground">
            We blend AI-assisted testing with human-friendly workflows so you
            can trust the software you release. Kyoto automates repetitive
            checks, highlights high-risk changes, and keeps your team aligned
            through clear insights.
          </p>
          <div class="grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2">
            <div class="rounded-lg border border-border/70 bg-muted/30 p-4">
              <p class="text-sm font-medium text-muted-foreground">Founded</p>
              <p class="text-2xl font-semibold text-foreground">2024</p>
            </div>
            <div class="rounded-lg border border-border/70 bg-muted/30 p-4">
              <p class="text-sm font-medium text-muted-foreground">Customers</p>
              <p class="text-2xl font-semibold text-foreground">
                Early partners
              </p>
            </div>
            <div
              class="rounded-lg border border-border/70 bg-muted/30 p-4 sm:col-span-2"
            >
              <p class="text-sm font-medium text-muted-foreground">Focus</p>
              <p class="text-lg font-semibold text-foreground">
                AI-powered quality assurance for modern product teams
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="border-b border-border/60 bg-muted/20">
      <div
        class="container grid gap-12 px-6 py-20 sm:px-8 lg:grid-cols-[1.2fr,1.8fr] lg:gap-16"
      >
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight sm:text-4xl">
            Why Kyoto exists
          </h2>
          <p class="text-base text-muted-foreground">
            Modern teams move fast, but quality practices haven&apos;t kept
            pace. Manual QA slows everything down and brittle automation breaks
            with every change. Kyoto gives teams the guardrails to release
            continuously without sacrificing confidence.
          </p>
        </div>
        <dl class="grid gap-6 sm:grid-cols-2">
          <div
            class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-background p-6 shadow-sm"
          >
            <dt
              class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-muted-foreground"
            >
              AI-guided coverage
            </dt>
            <dd class="mt-3 text-muted-foreground">
              Kyoto surfaces the highest-risk flows and generates meaningful
              test plans automatically, so your team catches the issues that
              matter before users do.
            </dd>
          </div>
          <div
            class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-background p-6 shadow-sm"
          >
            <dt
              class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-muted-foreground"
            >
              Collaborative insights
            </dt>
            <dd class="mt-3 text-muted-foreground">
              Everyone sees the same source of truth—from engineers to product
              managers—through rich dashboards, annotations, and release notes.
            </dd>
          </div>
          <div
            class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-background p-6 shadow-sm"
          >
            <dt
              class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-muted-foreground"
            >
              Continuous trust
            </dt>
            <dd class="mt-3 text-muted-foreground">
              Kyoto integrates into your CI/CD pipeline to guard every deploy,
              offering contextual alerts and deep links back to the exact commit
              or story.
            </dd>
          </div>
          <div
            class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-background p-6 shadow-sm"
          >
            <dt
              class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-muted-foreground"
            >
              Human-first automation
            </dt>
            <dd class="mt-3 text-muted-foreground">
              We augment your team rather than replace it, keeping review
              workflows transparent and creating space for experts to focus on
              higher leverage work.
            </dd>
          </div>
        </dl>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="border-b border-border/60 bg-background">
      <div
        class="container grid gap-12 px-6 py-20 sm:px-8 lg:grid-cols-[1.2fr,1.8fr] lg:gap-16"
      >
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight sm:text-4xl">
            Building with principles
          </h2>
          <p class="text-base text-muted-foreground">
            Kyoto is crafted by builders who value pragmatic automation, deep
            empathy for end users, and resilient systems. These principles guide
            every product decision.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="grid gap-6">
          <div class="rounded-2xl border border-border bg-card p-6 shadow-sm">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold">Empower teams, not silos</h3>
            <p class="mt-3 text-muted-foreground">
              We create shared context so QA, engineering, and product can
              collaborate in real time without handoffs or status meetings.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="rounded-2xl border border-border bg-card p-6 shadow-sm">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold">Bias toward clarity</h3>
            <p class="mt-3 text-muted-foreground">
              Every insight is actionable. Kyoto highlights root causes, impact,
              and next steps instead of burying teams in noise.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="rounded-2xl border border-border bg-card p-6 shadow-sm">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold">Secure by design</h3>
            <p class="mt-3 text-muted-foreground">
              We operate with enterprise-grade security practices and give
              customers control over their data lifecycles from day one.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="bg-muted/10">
      <div
        class="container grid gap-10 px-6 py-20 sm:px-8 lg:grid-cols-[1.1fr,1.9fr] lg:gap-16"
      >
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight sm:text-4xl">
            What&apos;s next
          </h2>
          <p class="text-base text-muted-foreground">
            We&apos;re working closely with design partners to shape
            Kyoto&apos;s roadmap. From proactive defect prediction to richer
            integrations, our mission is to make every release day feel
            boring—in the best way possible.
          </p>
          <a
            href="/upcoming-features"
            class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-md border border-border px-4 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-foreground transition-colors hover:bg-muted focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-ring focus-visible:ring-offset-2 focus-visible:ring-offset-background"
          >
            Explore upcoming features
          </a>
        </div>
        <div class="grid gap-8">
          <div
            class="relative rounded-3xl border border-border bg-background p-8"
          >
            <div
              class="absolute inset-0 -z-10 rounded-3xl bg-gradient-to-br from-primary/10 via-transparent to-transparent"
            >
            </div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold">Where we started</h3>
            <p class="mt-3 text-muted-foreground">
              Kyoto started as an internal tooling project to make release
              testing less painful. Sharing it with peers showed us how
              universal that pain is—and how hungry teams are for tools that
              amplify their judgment.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="rounded-3xl border border-border bg-background p-8">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold">Join us</h3>
            <p class="mt-3 text-muted-foreground">
              We&apos;re assembling a small, senior team across engineering,
              design, and customer partnerships. If our mission resonates,
              we&apos;d love to connect.
            </p>
            <a
              href="mailto:hello@kyoto.run"
              class="mt-6 inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-md bg-primary px-4 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-primary-foreground transition-colors hover:bg-primary/90 focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-ring focus-visible:ring-offset-2 focus-visible:ring-offset-background"
            >
              Say hello
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
  <LandingFooter />
</Layout>
